If the user sets the vertical align of a `BitmapFont` to either `VAlign.Center` or `VAlign.Bottom` it positions the text incorrectly. I'll only discuss `VAlign.Bottom` here.

For `VAglin.Bottom` the text is positioned _below_ the defined text box and renders downwards from there. Instead it should position the text at the bottom border of text box and render upwards.

Screenshot:
https://www.dropbox.com/s/2idcx1oxg4jrwl9/valign-bottom-incorrect.png?dl=0

The right text should be inside the blue box; the last line "touching" the bottom border.

The bug is probably caused by in incorrect calculation of `totalHeight` in method `Letters.validateSize()`.

